Wash and dry all produce. Trim, peel, and dice @carrot{3%ounce}. Halve, peel, and
dice @yellow onion{1}(halved, peeled, and diced). Mince or grate @garlic{2%clove}. Halve
@demi-baguette{1}(halved lengthwise).

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a #medium pot{} (use a #large pot{} for
4 servings) over medium-high heat. Add carrot, onion, and half the garlic; season
with @salt{1/2%tsp} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until veggies are tender,
~{5-6%minutes}.

Add @tomato paste{1.5%ounce} to #pot{}; stir to combine, ~{30%seconds}. Stir in
@diced tomatoes{14%ounce}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}(crushed), @mushroom stock concentrate{1},
@Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon}, and @water{2.5%cups}. Cover and bring to a boil.

Once soup is boiling, reduce heat to medium and uncover. Season with salt
@salt{1/2%tsp} and pepper. Gently stir in @cheese tortelloni{9%ounce}. Cook,
uncovered, until pasta is tender, ~{7-9%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Meanwhile, toast baguette until golden. Place @butter{1%tablespoon} and remaining
garlic in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave in ~{10%second} intervals
until softened. Season with a pinch of salt and pepper. Spread onto cut sides
of baguette.

Divide soup between bowls; top with @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}. Serve with garlic
bread on the side.

> This hearty, soul-warming soup is chock full of goodness—carrot, onion, diced
> tomatoes, tender cheese tortelloni, and a sprinkle of Parm. Get ready for a meal
> as satisfying as it is delicious.